through the menu MEET THE TEAM KATHERINE FRENCH Founder & CEO Katherine completed her BA at Boston University in , a PhD in Plant Sciences at the University of Oxford in , and two postdocs at UC Berkeley and Lawrence Berkeley National Lab between She has published over a dozen scientific papers and received grants from governmental, charitable, and industrial sources to support her She has received a number of awards recognizing her research, including the prestigious British Marshall Her areas of expertise include environmental engineering, bioremediation, ecology and sustainable She previously developed the first ever bacteria that can ‘eat’ petroleum and cleaned up contaminated soil and water from a former Shell Oil Refinery from Bay Point, She founded BluumBio in as a platform to develop the next generation of bioremediation technologies that will clean up historic and emerging pollutants from the Outside of work, Katherine is an avid cyclist and ballet dancer and enjoys exploring the Bay DREW HENDRICKSON Head of Organism Discovery and Assay Development Drew is a gay scientist working in Microbial He received his Bachelor’s degrees from UC Berkeley in Chemical Biology and Microbial Biology with During this time, Drew researched the bioremediation potential for to degrade petroleum hydrocarbons, for which he received his department s grant for Drew then joined the Lawrence Berkeley National Lab from to develop a framework for ecology in a subsurface watershed contaminated with from the Manhattan His expertise is in analytical chemistry, microbial characterization, and In his free time, he loves cultivating bizarre organisms, from orchids and carnivorous plants, to bioluminescent microbes and AZION WHITE Biochemist & Synthetic Biologist Azion White is a graduate from the University of Minnesota, where he received a BS in biochemistry and worked as a research associate for the University’s BioTechnology He has experience in synthetic biology from various projects, including the characterization and assembly of a biocatalyst toolbox for lignin degradation to the design of recombinant proteins to make biodegradable coatings for He’s passionate about the vast applications of synthetic biology and its potential to propel the development of technology and the society that benefits from JORDAN BAKER Bioengineering and Bioprocess Development Jordan grew up on a farm outside of Philadelphia, Pennsylvania and received a Bachelor s and Master s degree in Chemical & Biomolecular Engineering from Johns Hopkins While at Johns Hopkins, he performed research into genetically modified algae for biofuels and high value chemical After graduation, Jordan worked at Genentech in South San Francisco for three years before starting a PhD program in Bioengineering at UC Berkeley & UCSF where his research is focused on building synthetic biology and metabolic engineering tools for environmental and sustainability Outside of work, Jordan loves to spend time with his dog, explore the outdoors, cook, and play ©2021 by Proudly created with   Knowledge Center | BluumBio BLUUMBIO Home About Knowledge Center FAQ Contact Meet the Team More Use tab to navigate through the menu KNOWLEDGE CENTER WHAT ARE ENZYMES? Enzymes are proteins found in You use enzymes to digest your food and perform a host of other reactions that allow you grow and In nature, bacteria, plants, algae and fungi have specialized enzymes that transform what we consider toxins and , carcinogenic dyes, heavy metals, arsenic, and plastic, to name a This carbon gives these organisms life and helps power the complex interactions which drive healthy WHAT IS SYNTHETIC BIOLOGY? All living things are made of, and run by, DNA . DNA is the code, or directions, which tell an organism how to grow, develop and interact with the Using technologies inspired by nature, we can edit this code to develop new organisms that can help us clean up the To learn how synthetic biology can help build more sustainable societies, read this article by our Check out how we sped up oil spill clean up here . WHY ARE BLUUMBIO S SOLUTIONS BETTER FOR THE ENVIRONMENT? Our technologies do not use harsh chemicals and minimally disturb the natural environment in which they are In addition, our enzymes degrade and or sequester target Traditional methods, like soil removal or capping, do not solve the problem, they just remove it from How is BluumBio different? We don t just remove contaminants from the environment: we restore degraded ©2021 by Proudly created with   Bioremediation | BluumBio | Berkeley BLUUMBIO Home About Knowle

Growth Insights & Strategy | Healthy Insights top of page Home Our Expertise Demand Intelligence Competitive Intelligence Growth Insights & Strategy Customer Segmentation Sales Effectiveness Execution HTH360 Industries We Serve Insights for Growth Contact More Use tab to navigate through the menu Growth Insights & Strategy Use data to identify and prioritize the key paths for growth Strategy is more about what you choose not to do than what you choose to do - data helps prioritize and create focus for those decisions For the past + years, our leaders have been helping companies design, build and deploy growth Over this time, we ve come to learn that strategy has different meanings in different For some, it means "plan" (the specific actions we will take to move from A to B), for others it means "hope" (the vision we aspire to get to) and for the rest it means "choice" (the proactive decision about what we choose to do and what we don t choose to do). ​ In our experience, strategy really is all about decision making and choice It s about understanding the different options that exist and making deliberate choices to invest and execute a select number of those options while making a deliberate choice to stop doing other It s about understanding the implications of "Choice A" "Choice B". Make no mistake, choosing to ignore decisions about what not to stop is still a choice - one that uses valuable resources for ​ Failures in strategy are often the result of not understanding this choice architecture and the different implications of starting and stopping Failures result from resources being spread too thin across too many initiatives or from being overly focused on a single element of the strategy that the rest of the organization gets ​ Having a deep understanding of the revenue model and using data to inform the implications of choice can help leaders make better strategic USING DATA TO DEVELOP A STRATEGY FOR ADDRESSING TURNOVER Over the past few years, the labor market in healthcare has been extremely tight, especially for frontline The challenge with high turnover though is that it can have a direct impact on clinical care - so managing turnover is a key strategic issue for most care To do this is not a simple, Turnover is a issue in most companies and different solutions are needed to holistically address the This is where data can come Using internal data, we helped this large autism company identify new insights with regards to turnover and develop a targeted set of solutions that s directly reducing turnover Read the Case Study Need help leveraging data to drive growth? partners and employees), diversity (creating meaningful opportunities for women and people of color) and cause (a percentage of profits will be donated to various nonprofit causes), Next League is proud to lean into its positioning as a talent and “Dave, Mike, and their entire team have spent many years delivering great results and the highest level of service for some of the most important sports and media properties in the world,” said Doug Perlman, Founder and CEO of Sports Media Advisors, who also sits on the Next League Advisory “I know the sports ecosystem will be excited about this latest venture it’s never been more needed than it is right ” Next League’s other Advisory Board members include Alysse Soll (Chair, Women in Sports Tech and Deal of the Harvard Business School Alternative assets are assets that are not categorized as stocks, bonds or While there are alternative assets traded on the stock market, you will never find any of those assets in any of our The reason is We believe that alternative assets can play a prominent role in achieving a conservative yield only if the assets do not have direct Wall Street Within the alternative asset industry, SIH Capital Group primarily focuses on commercial real Why Commercial Real Estate?
